reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for both grandson 1.5yrs and granddaughter 3.5yrs
reviews.reviewText: Great detail and size. Seem very sturdy. Noisy but not consistently. Great gifts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My little boy turned one and we bought him these for a present as we didn’t have much for trucks or cars for him. He played with these all night, from the lights, the sounds and they even go by themselves kept him entertained. With being little, and not understanding about to be nice with toys quite yet- they have held up well! No pieces broken and no tires have come off! Fun set to play with and will definitely be ordering these again for future presents.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very realistic emergency vehicles
reviews.reviewText: I gave these to my 2 year old grandson for Christmas and he loves them. They are one of his favorite toys. The noise and lights are very realistic. They are durable too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy Toys As My Toddler Has Skated On Them :o
reviews.reviewText: Yeah, my toddler has skated on them, and they survived! There's not even a chip of plastic broken on these toys from rough use. However, it is possible to remove the trunk from the police car. Though it doesn't take away from the play-ability of these toys.The minor complaint I have about these toys is the lights. They don't represent American emergency vehicles. I mean the ambulance and fire engine, have two blue lights and the helicopter has a search light and rear propeller light. And they're all DIM! Though kids might not care about these minor details as much as me, LOL

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Glad i bought two sets.
